critique: This document is an executive order that delays certain transfers, consolidations, and eliminations provided for under section 4 of Executive Order No. 6166 of June 10, 1933, as amended, be further delayed beyond the effective date of that order. It pertains to economic regulation and government intervention, specifically regarding the function of disbursement now exercised by United States Marshals under the Department of Justice. There is no information about immigration, executive power, federalism, national security vs. civil liberties, or social inclusion. The ideological tilt is neutral.
